import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='precipitation', kde=True, color='blue', bins=30)
    plt.axvline(data['precipitation'].median(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f"Median: {data['precipitation'].median():.2f}")
    plt.title("What is the distribution of precipitation?", wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]

    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
    sns.lineplot(x='date', y='temp_max', data=data, label='Max Temperature', color='red')
    sns.lineplot(x='date', y='temp_min', data=data, label='Min Temperature', color='blue')
    plt.title('How does temperature vary over time?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Date')
    plt.ylabel('Temperature (°C)')
    plt.legend()
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.scatterplot(data=data, x='wind', y='precipitation', hue='weather')
    plt.title('What is the relationship between wind and precipitation?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend(title='Weather', loc='upper right')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    weather_counts = data['weather'].value_counts()
    sns.barplot(x=weather_counts.index, y=weather_counts.values)
    plt.xlabel('Weather Conditions')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the most common weather condition in Seattle?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend(weather_counts.index, title='Weather Conditions', loc='upper right')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]

    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.boxplot(x='weather', y='temp_max', data=data, palette='Set2')
    sns.boxplot(x='weather', y='temp_min', data=data, palette='Set2')
    plt.title('How does temperature affect the weather condition?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend(['Temp Max', 'Temp Min'], loc='upper left')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
